WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.047 --> 00:00:08.049
[sinister music playing]

2
00:00:11.928 --> 00:00:16.099
[Camila sighs] Oh. yeah. I recognize her.
Her name's Rebecca Cross.

3
00:00:16.182 --> 00:00:17.934
She goes by Becky.

4
00:00:18.018 --> 00:00:20.437
Miguel hired her to babysit his children.

5
00:00:21.187 --> 00:00:22.313
Okay. [exhales]

6
00:00:22.397 --> 00:00:23.982
So I was over there stretching.

7
00:00:24.065 --> 00:00:27.736
and I was about to start rehearsing
when she came and whacked me from behind.

8
00:00:27.819 --> 00:00:30.780
She had a mask over her face.
a black one with a beak.

9
00:00:30.864 --> 00:00:32.741
I pulled it off. and I saw it was Becky.

10
00:00:32.824 --> 00:00:35.076
- We started fighting.
- [sighs]

11
00:00:35.160 --> 00:00:37.746
Then she choked me.
and I hit her with a light.

12
00:00:38.413 --> 00:00:40.957
I was calling you guys
when she disappeared.

13
00:00:41.750 --> 00:00:44.085
- Is she injured?
- It's possible.

14
00:00:46.629 --> 00:00:48.214
[theme music playing]

15
00:00:49.215 --> 00:00:51.342
FAKE PROFILE

16
00:00:51.426 --> 00:00:52.343
[music fades]

17
00:00:54.054 --> 00:00:56.431
- [cell phone ringing]
- [Ángela] Okay. it's them.

18
00:00:58.641 --> 00:00:59.768
It is? You sure?

19
00:00:59.851 --> 00:01:01.311
Hello! Talk to me.

20
00:01:01.394 --> 00:01:02.937
[kidnapper. voice modified] <i>We have Eva.</i>

21
00:01:03.021 --> 00:01:07.525
<i>If you want to see her alive again.</i>
<i>give us $2 million at 4:30 a.m. sharp.</i>

22
00:01:08.026 --> 00:01:09.235
<i>No cops.</i>

23
00:01:09.319 --> 00:01:11.196
<i>Just you and your husband.</i>

24
00:01:11.279 --> 00:01:12.280
<i>Is that clear?</i>

25
00:01:12.363 --> 00:01:14.741
Okay. Uh. where do we meet?

26
00:01:14.824 --> 00:01:17.452
<i>If you don't have all the money at 4:30.</i>
<i>you'll get a sign.</i>

27
00:01:18.620 --> 00:01:20.580
<i>It will be part of your daughter's body.</i>

28
00:01:20.663 --> 00:01:23.291
No. no. no. no. That won't be necessary.

29
00:01:23.374 --> 00:01:27.003
Tell me where you want the cash delivered.
and I'll be there. bitch.

30
00:01:29.005 --> 00:01:29.839
Hello?

31
00:01:31.174 --> 00:01:32.050
Hello?

32
00:01:32.926 --> 00:01:33.885
Fuck!

33
00:01:33.968 --> 00:01:37.806
[tense music plays]

34
00:01:40.141 --> 00:01:41.267
I swear I'm terrified

35
00:01:41.351 --> 00:01:44.729
that this awful psychotic bitch
will just show up at the club.

36
00:01:46.523 --> 00:01:48.024
So you think she'll come back?

37
00:01:49.025 --> 00:01:50.485
I'm convinced she will.

38
00:01:50.985 --> 00:01:53.363
She's got problems
with something at the club.

39
00:01:54.072 --> 00:01:55.740
She killed Salomé.

40
00:01:56.241 --> 00:01:59.619
After that. she went after Noa.
then Moira. then attacked me.

41
00:02:00.662 --> 00:02:01.913
Cami. look at me.

42
00:02:04.833 --> 00:02:05.959
Let me help you.

43
00:02:07.585 --> 00:02:08.586
You have to stop.

44
00:02:08.670 --> 00:02:11.172
["Arráncame Las Ganas (Primer Conjuro)"
by Duina Del Mar playing]

45
00:02:11.256 --> 00:02:13.299
<i>Every caress serves a purpose.</i>

46
00:02:13.883 --> 00:02:15.552
<i>It awakens sensitivity.</i>

47
00:02:17.554 --> 00:02:18.680
<i>It releases tension.</i>

48
00:02:19.389 --> 00:02:21.683
<i>Your body and mind become harmonious.</i>

49
00:02:22.183 --> 00:02:23.393
<i>There's no rush.</i>

50
00:02:24.561 --> 00:02:26.104
<i>There are no expectations.</i>

51
00:02:27.147 --> 00:02:28.648
<i>No obligations.</i>

52
00:02:30.942 --> 00:02:33.528
<i>We honor and worship the erotic.</i>

53
00:02:34.195 --> 00:02:37.448
<i>It's the sacred language of our bodies.</i>

54
00:02:37.532 --> 00:02:40.201
["Arráncame Las Ganas (Primer Conjuro)"
continues]

55
00:03:04.767 --> 00:03:06.519
- [music ends]
- [cell phone ringing]

56
00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:13.526
Hello?

57
00:03:13.610 --> 00:03:14.861
[Becky] <i>Ángela.</i>

58
00:03:14.944 --> 00:03:15.904
<i>It's Becky.</i>

59
00:03:15.987 --> 00:03:18.781
<i>I need to talk to you right now.</i>
<i>Please let me in.</i>

60
00:03:18.865 --> 00:03:20.491
You know I have nowhere else to go.

61
00:03:21.075 --> 00:03:23.870
Hmm. This is not my problem.

62
00:03:25.872 --> 00:03:27.999
But you are a relentless one.

63
00:03:29.918 --> 00:03:31.002
Go away.

64
00:03:32.503 --> 00:03:34.672
Don't make me call the police.

65
00:03:35.506 --> 00:03:36.424
Mmm.

66
00:03:38.927 --> 00:03:40.053
I wouldn't.

67
00:03:40.136 --> 00:03:41.387
Calling the police?

68
00:03:42.847 --> 00:03:44.015
Not a good plan.

69
00:03:44.098 --> 00:03:45.058
No?

70
00:03:45.558 --> 00:03:46.559
Why's that?

71
00:03:48.519 --> 00:03:50.396
Who do you think they're gonna believe?

72
00:03:50.897 --> 00:03:51.731
Me…

73
00:03:53.900 --> 00:03:54.984
or a poor addict

74
00:03:55.068 --> 00:03:58.238
who was willing to sell her baby
just to buy more crack?

75
00:03:58.321 --> 00:03:59.155
Think about it.

76
00:04:01.950 --> 00:04:04.285
- [Becky screams]
- [screams]

77
00:04:04.953 --> 00:04:06.704
You're fucking dead!

78
00:04:06.788 --> 00:04:08.915
- [Lucas grunts]
- [Ángela screams]

79
00:04:08.998 --> 00:04:10.208
Get off me!

80
00:04:10.917 --> 00:04:12.877
[Ángela wincing]

81
00:04:16.214 --> 00:04:17.131
[Ángela screaming]

82
00:04:27.684 --> 00:04:29.310
[music ends]

83
00:04:29.394 --> 00:04:30.937
- Becky.
- [gasps]

84
00:04:32.021 --> 00:04:32.981
[Ángela] Lucas!

85
00:04:33.064 --> 00:04:34.315
[Lucas] Come on. get up.

86
00:04:35.024 --> 00:04:36.859
- [Ángela] Lucas!
- We're leaving. We have to go.

87
00:04:37.443 --> 00:04:38.861
- [Becky] What happened?
- [Ángela] Lucas!

88
00:04:38.945 --> 00:04:40.613
Not now. We don't have time for questions.

89
00:04:40.697 --> 00:04:41.906
- We have to go.
- [Ángela] Lucas!

90
00:04:41.990 --> 00:04:43.199
- Come on.
- [Becky groans]

91
00:04:45.618 --> 00:04:46.828
[Ángela] Lucas!

92
00:04:48.204 --> 00:04:49.205
- Let's go.
- Okay.

93
00:04:50.248 --> 00:04:51.499
[whimpers. screams]

94
00:04:51.582 --> 00:04:52.875
Shit! What's going on. Ángela?

95
00:04:52.959 --> 00:04:54.836
- What happened? Oh. wow.
- [panting] No.

96
00:04:54.919 --> 00:04:55.837
I'll help you. okay?

97
00:04:55.920 --> 00:04:58.214
Yeah. yeah. take it easy. take it easy.
Calm down. I got ya.

98
00:04:58.298 --> 00:04:59.632
Okay. Ángela? Shit!

99
00:05:00.550 --> 00:05:01.551
What happened?

100
00:05:01.634 --> 00:05:03.052
Where's Lucas?

101
00:05:03.136 --> 00:05:04.012
[Ángela] Lucas!

102
00:05:04.512 --> 00:05:06.973
Okay. I got you. I got you.
Take it easy. take it easy.

103
00:05:07.056 --> 00:05:07.890
I'm here.

104
00:05:07.974 --> 00:05:10.184
- [screaming]
- [repeating] Yeah.

105
00:05:10.268 --> 00:05:11.311
Okay.

106
00:05:11.811 --> 00:05:13.354
[Ángela sobbing]

107
00:05:14.814 --> 00:05:18.234
You ever think something like this
would happen to the two of us?

108
00:05:21.654 --> 00:05:22.488
No.

109
00:05:24.490 --> 00:05:25.491
Not once.

110
00:05:27.076 --> 00:05:28.411
Sometimes…

111
00:05:30.997 --> 00:05:33.499
I think it's all a nightmare.
but it's not.

112
00:05:36.210 --> 00:05:37.295
It's all real.

113
00:05:39.797 --> 00:05:40.631
[Ángela] Hmm.

114
00:05:41.841 --> 00:05:44.635
Now we wait
for those monsters to call us back.

115
00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:50.224
Go to sleep.

116
00:05:53.394 --> 00:05:54.228
I won't.

117
00:05:54.312 --> 00:05:56.314
[intriguing music playing]

118
00:06:23.674 --> 00:06:25.551
<i>♪ Why did you go? ♪</i>

119
00:06:31.224 --> 00:06:35.645
<i>♪ Why did you go? ♪</i>

120
00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:47.615
[vocalizing]

121
00:06:56.040 --> 00:06:59.460
<i>♪ Why did you go? ♪</i>

122
00:07:03.673 --> 00:07:06.342
<i>♪ Why did you go? ♪</i>

123
00:07:11.305 --> 00:07:13.224
<i>♪ Why did you go? ♪</i>

124
00:07:13.307 --> 00:07:14.392
[Ángela moans]

125
00:07:18.938 --> 00:07:21.774
<i>♪ Why did you go? ♪</i>

126
00:07:28.614 --> 00:07:29.699
[Ángela moaning]

127
00:07:31.909 --> 00:07:34.203
- [music ends]
- [cell phone ringing]

128
00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:39.333
[inhales]

129
00:07:40.251 --> 00:07:41.419
[winces]

130
00:07:42.253 --> 00:07:43.254
[groans]

131
00:07:44.172 --> 00:07:47.133
- [Miguel] Oh shit. It's them.
- [groans]

132
00:07:47.216 --> 00:07:48.676
- Okay.
- [Ángela] Hello?

133
00:07:49.177 --> 00:07:51.846
[kidnapper] <i>The drop-off location is</i>
<i>at the San Juan dock.</i>

134
00:07:51.929 --> 00:07:53.473
<i>It is now 3:30 in the morning.</i>

135
00:07:53.973 --> 00:07:55.475
[dramatic sting]

136
00:07:56.309 --> 00:07:58.060
[Miguel] Let's go.
I'll help you get dressed.

137
00:08:01.731 --> 00:08:04.567
- [engine revving]
- [tires squealing]

138
00:08:04.650 --> 00:08:06.152
[tense music playing]

139
00:08:12.283 --> 00:08:14.660
Okay. We're at your location. What now?

140
00:08:15.953 --> 00:08:18.289
[kidnapper] <i>Leave the briefcase</i>
<i>on the hood of your car.</i>

141
00:08:21.459 --> 00:08:23.336
And then who will give us our daughter?

142
00:08:23.836 --> 00:08:25.004
<i>You have to trust me.</i>

143
00:08:25.505 --> 00:08:28.633
<i>You do what I say. and you'll be</i>
<i>hugging your daughter in no time.</i>

144
00:08:36.015 --> 00:08:36.974
Okay. now what?

145
00:08:37.517 --> 00:08:39.477
<i>You see the dock? Walk to it.</i>

146
00:08:39.560 --> 00:08:40.728
<i>All the way to the end.</i>

147
00:08:44.190 --> 00:08:47.485
[Miguel] Okay. we're on our way.
but I don't see her.

148
00:08:48.194 --> 00:08:49.111
Where is she?

149
00:08:52.073 --> 00:08:53.366
<i>Your daughter is very close.</i>

150
00:08:53.449 --> 00:08:55.159
<i>In fact. she's under your feet.</i>

151
00:08:57.370 --> 00:08:58.829
[Miguel] Where is she? Where?

152
00:08:58.913 --> 00:09:00.706
Eva! Eva! Can you hear me?!

153
00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:04.001
[exhales]

154
00:09:05.586 --> 00:09:06.629
[Ángela] Eva!

155
00:09:07.421 --> 00:09:08.756
- Eva!
- [Ángela] Oh my God!

156
00:09:09.382 --> 00:09:10.341
Eva!

157
00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:13.052
- There she is!
- My baby!

158
00:09:14.136 --> 00:09:15.012
Oh. my baby!

159
00:09:15.805 --> 00:09:17.181
- No. no. no. no!
- Almost!

160
00:09:18.266 --> 00:09:20.017
[Ángela gasps]

161
00:09:20.101 --> 00:09:21.185
[Miguel grunting]

162
00:09:23.646 --> 00:09:25.022
[Ángela] Oh my God! Is she…

163
00:09:25.106 --> 00:09:26.065
What is that?

164
00:09:26.983 --> 00:09:28.734
What the fuck?!

165
00:09:28.818 --> 00:09:29.694
[Miguel grunts]

166
00:09:29.777 --> 00:09:31.153
[melancholy music playing]

167
00:09:33.239 --> 00:09:35.575
[sobbing]

168
00:09:45.001 --> 00:09:46.210
[rat squeaking]

169
00:09:47.420 --> 00:09:48.379
[door opens]

170
00:09:56.470 --> 00:09:57.805
- [stomps]
- [rat screeches]

171
00:10:05.938 --> 00:10:07.315
[keys jangling]

172
00:10:08.107 --> 00:10:09.984
[gate locks]

173
00:10:19.160 --> 00:10:20.578
[engine revving]

174
00:10:20.661 --> 00:10:22.663
[tense music playing]

175
00:10:26.917 --> 00:10:27.960
[music ends]

176
00:10:36.260 --> 00:10:37.303
How is our Eva?

177
00:10:39.347 --> 00:10:41.057
She's asking about her father.

178
00:10:42.516 --> 00:10:43.893
And how are you doing?

179
00:10:48.105 --> 00:10:50.107
It's good of you to join us. Juan David.

180
00:10:51.651 --> 00:10:54.362
That feeling in your chest and stomach
when you can't breathe.

181
00:10:54.445 --> 00:10:55.363
that feeling is hatred.

182
00:10:57.490 --> 00:10:59.492
Hatred is a very powerful emotion.

183
00:10:59.575 --> 00:11:00.743
It's as strong as love.

184
00:11:01.410 --> 00:11:02.453
But you should be careful

185
00:11:02.536 --> 00:11:05.790
because if you can't handle it.
it will destroy you.

186
00:11:08.417 --> 00:11:09.585
This is your moment.

187
00:11:11.087 --> 00:11:13.214
It's time for you to get even. Juan David.

188
00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:15.341
You should enjoy it.

189
00:11:16.801 --> 00:11:18.511
You just have to let yourself go.

190
00:11:22.723 --> 00:11:24.308
Here are the keys to the cabin.

191
00:11:26.352 --> 00:11:29.021
[suspenseful music playing]

192
00:11:38.239 --> 00:11:41.617
Well. this is
exactly what I need right now.

193
00:11:48.791 --> 00:11:52.044
I want to toast you all. my collaborators.

194
00:11:52.128 --> 00:11:53.003
<i>Salud.</i>

195
00:11:53.629 --> 00:11:56.674
[Joanna] <i>Salud.</i>
This is all because of you. Ángela.

196
00:11:57.258 --> 00:11:59.260
[clinking]

197
00:12:00.428 --> 00:12:02.638
So what'd you do with Becky?

198
00:12:02.722 --> 00:12:07.476
Mmm. So. Becky is no longer with us.

199
00:12:07.977 --> 00:12:10.563
The police are searching for her
in connection with the murders.

200
00:12:10.646 --> 00:12:13.107
Really. who cares? I'm so bored with that.

201
00:12:13.190 --> 00:12:16.068
All that matters is
that we accomplished our mission.

202
00:12:16.861 --> 00:12:20.114
[Oliver] Miguel and Camila broke up.
and they are never getting back together.

203
00:12:20.197 --> 00:12:21.365
This is just what you wanted.

204
00:12:21.449 --> 00:12:23.534
Yeah. it worked perfectly.

205
00:12:24.201 --> 00:12:27.329
I had to hit him
where it hurts him the hardest.

206
00:12:28.122 --> 00:12:28.998
Unfortunately for him.

207
00:12:29.081 --> 00:12:32.501
his Achilles heel just happens to be.
well. my daughter. Eva.

208
00:12:33.002 --> 00:12:34.628
[dramatic music playing]

209
00:12:44.889 --> 00:12:49.518
<i>♪ So do you know</i>
<i>Who's your enemy or your friend? ♪</i>

210
00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:53.898
<i>♪ For there is no way of knowing</i>
<i>How this will end ♪</i>

211
00:12:53.981 --> 00:12:55.608
<i>♪ Though you endure ♪</i>

212
00:12:55.691 --> 00:12:57.610
<i>♪ One thing is sure ♪</i>

213
00:12:57.693 --> 00:13:03.324
<i>♪ You're never secure ♪</i>

214
00:13:03.407 --> 00:13:04.241
[music ends]

215
00:13:05.034 --> 00:13:06.118
Speaking of Eva.

216
00:13:06.702 --> 00:13:09.622
would you please tell them
to set her free.

217
00:13:09.705 --> 00:13:12.541
I'm dying to see her
and tell her that everything's fine.

218
00:13:12.625 --> 00:13:14.210
and that it's over now.

219
00:13:22.301 --> 00:13:23.344
[Ángela sighs]

220
00:13:23.427 --> 00:13:24.762
I'm not made of stone.

221
00:13:25.471 --> 00:13:27.556
I know. David. I've been there.

222
00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:30.184
It was painful at first. At first.

223
00:13:31.519 --> 00:13:33.562
So when does it stop hurting

224
00:13:33.646 --> 00:13:36.273
after someone has caused
so much suffering?

225
00:13:38.317 --> 00:13:40.027
So in my experience.

226
00:13:40.611 --> 00:13:41.987
it's when the tables are turned.

227
00:13:42.071 --> 00:13:43.739
It's the law of equilibrium.

228
00:13:43.823 --> 00:13:46.617
Balance is restored.
and now it's your turn.

229
00:13:46.700 --> 00:13:47.743
so have a good time.

230
00:13:47.827 --> 00:13:49.453
[tense music playing]

231
00:13:49.537 --> 00:13:51.872
I know it was
one of the worst moments of your life.

232
00:13:51.956 --> 00:13:53.332
and it's still a nightmare for you.

233
00:13:53.415 --> 00:13:57.211
<i>So if you ever want to get revenge</i>
<i>on Camila for that shit she pulled on you.</i>

234
00:13:57.294 --> 00:13:58.504
<i>come find me.</i>

235
00:13:58.587 --> 00:14:00.923
I'm not interested in cash.
or revenge. or anything.

236
00:14:04.218 --> 00:14:06.011
No. What you're seeking is justice.

237
00:14:06.887 --> 00:14:09.056
<i>- Crime and punishment.</i>
<i>- </i>[screaming]

238
00:14:09.974 --> 00:14:13.477
<i>The two of them have to pay</i>
<i>for all the damage they caused us.</i>

239
00:14:13.561 --> 00:14:15.145
- [screaming]
<i>- </i>[David] <i>Done.</i>

240
00:14:15.229 --> 00:14:18.774
There's everything you asked for.
Empty cans and food for several days.

241
00:14:19.733 --> 00:14:22.945
Great. now hit me.
Hit me hard. Right in my face.

242
00:14:23.028 --> 00:14:24.822
No. I'm doing that.

243
00:14:25.406 --> 00:14:26.365
[Ángela] <i>You're so weak.</i>

244
00:14:35.875 --> 00:14:36.959
[exhales]

245
00:14:37.042 --> 00:14:38.377
[grunts]

246
00:14:54.643 --> 00:14:55.477
[Oliver] Ángela.

247
00:14:57.104 --> 00:14:59.648
- What's up?
- [Oliver] Eva's being taken to the island.

248
00:14:59.732 --> 00:15:01.275
{\an8}[suspenseful music playing]

249
00:15:15.456 --> 00:15:20.085
{\an8}DESIDERIO ISLAND

